  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b85\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0b9c\u0bc1\u0ba9 \u0bae\u0b95\u0bc7\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b89\u0bb3\u0bcd\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f 10 \u0baa\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0b8e\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0b95 \u0ba4\u0bca\u0b9f\u0bb0\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0bb3\u0bcd\u0bb3 \u0bb5\u0bb4\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8 \u0bae\u0bc1\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0ba9\u0bc6\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0b9a\u0bc6\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0bb2 \u0bae\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bc1 :\u00a0\u00a0\u0baa\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b85\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bc8 \u0b86\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bc7\u0baa\u0ba9\u0bae\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Case against 10 defendants including Arjuna Mahendran cannot proceed : Basic Objection on behalf of defendants",
      "author": "Digital Desk 5",
      "body_lines": [
        "Regarding the central bank bond fraud (2015), the defense attorney has submitted written arguments against the case filed against 10 defendants, including the former central bank governor Arjuna Mahendran, who cannot proceed on behalf of the defendants.",
        "When the said case came up for hearing on July 4, the government's senior lawyer Uthara Karunathilaka submitted the relevant arguments in the court.",
        "The Attorney General filed 23 charges against 10 defendants, including former Central Bank Governor Arjuna Mahendran, owner of Perpetual Treasuries, Arjun Aloysius, chairman of Perpetual Treasuries, in connection with the Central Bank's bond auction on September 27, 2015, which cost the government 688 million rupees. The case filed separately (04) came up for hearing on Monday.",
        "First, the case was taken up for hearing in the Special High Court before the permanent three-member Special High Court Judges Samba Janaki Rajaratne, Tamit Towawatta and Namal Palalle.",
        "During this, the first respondent, former Central Bank Governor Arjuna Mahendran, and the 10th respondent, Ajahn Bunjihewa, who served as the Director of Personal Treasuries, were present in the court.",
        "Meanwhile, on April 29, the main objection raised by the President's lawyer Anil Silva that the case could not be proceeded with, and written submissions were made on behalf of the suspects, the senior state lawyer Udara Karunathilaka, on behalf of the Attorney General, presented the counterarguments on behalf of the said objection. 4) submitted.",
        "In this situation, if there are any responses regarding the arguments of the Attorney General, the judges ordered to put them before the court during the upcoming term of the case and adjourned the case till the upcoming July 21.",
        "The First Permanent Triumvirate High Court of Western Province has already allowed the investigation of this case to proceed without the former Central Bank Governor Arjuna Mahendran and the tenth defendant, Ajahn Guardia Punjihewa.",
        "It is noteworthy that the court has decided to hear the allegations against the defendants Arjuna Mahendran and Ajahn Guardia Punjihewa in their absence while they are neglecting to appear in court on behalf of the Attorney General under Chapter 450 (8) of the Criminal Code."
      ],
